cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category as it proposes an extension to a binary neural network. It could also belong to the Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories as it discusses learning and retrieval rules. The paper's focus on networks and cliques could also place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. Finally, the simulation results mentioned in the abstract suggest that the paper could also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) category.
